reviews.text: This place offers a variety of options, with weekday specials, and weekday events. The pizza is not your typical pizza and has a different cheese so expect something different when you get pizza here. They have pizza and burger specials. The burgers and pizza are good, unfortunately we came here one time and were served a burnt pizza which was very disappointing. The crab dip was delicious, I recommend trying it. I also came for trivia one night and the host unfortunately said a lot of slurs that are not appropriate and most of my party was very offended, so I do not recommend coming in for trivia night. The booths are small and fit 4 people, there is a small enclosed outdoor seating area and the parking is down the street for when the parking lot gets full.

The king of the Maryland pizza. Half price pizza on Mondays and Tuesdays is hard to beat.  Fantastic happy hour selections as well. I would try the blackened Thai wings, crab pretzel, curly fries with a side of queso.
Great place! Both myself, friends and family have been going here for 20+ years. Fantastic people, service and food. Top notch pizza too.

I've lived in the area for 50 years, and my friend and I finally visited the location in Silver Spring. I went there for the pizza and I can honestly say it's among the best pizza you'll find anywhere! The sauce, crust, sausage and cheese combined to delight my taste buds. Our waitress was pleasant and extremely helpful. My buddy had the steak and cheese and absolutely loved it. I highly recommend this place. I wish it was closer to where I live so I could eat there more often.

Pizza is fabulous!  Servers are attentive and quick.  Very busy on Mondays and Tuesdays, half price pizza night.  The ambience has been the same for years...but very decent for families and friend groups.  Noisy and fun!

The subway 12335 Georgia Ave silver spring Md, one of the best subway. They are very clean and good to eat there with family. Their vegetables quality is fresh. They are backing bread every day and fresh smell when you enter the store. I recommend whoever like subway visit the store.

Walked in to this subway in the Glenmont shopping center and was greated upon opening the door. First is was a hello followed by I will be with you shortly. The short young lady by the name of Lily has great customer service. Was very assertive on my order in and out quick... Thank you Lily
An subway employee gave me less meat because I used a coupon this is one of the worst subways in the state of Maryland
This subway is clean and employees are very polite and serve you fast...it's look like after Changed in the ownership there is a pleasant Changed in service..
This restaurant is clean, employees are quick and service is fast. Looks like after changed in management everything is good. I would suggest this place .

Once every few years, I make the mistake of giving Pizza Hut another chance. Once upon a time, it used to be the best of the national franchises. It has become the worst -- no matter what location I use. The so-called pepperoni lovers pizza I ordered certainly was not filled with the amount of toppings the photo showed or menu listing claimed. The crust tasted like a combination of sponge and air. And the buffalo wings were so disgusting I had to throw them away. The alleged chicken meat was nasty, as was the buffalo sauce. Was that even real chicken? Shame on me, though, for giving Pizza Hut a chance. That was definitely my last-ever purchase there.

I wasn’t going to complain about this initially, but I decided I should inform you.

The staff to include the manager were not wearing masks or gloves to prepare or package food. Also, the staff preparing food were not wearing head coverings.    This was alarming to see when people are still catching Covid and it’s variations, Influenza, Common Cold and Respiratory Syncytial Virus (RSV) Viruses.

The manager wanted to argue the point that although he was not wearing gloves he was only bending the foil around a food container and did not touch any food.  The manager decided to wash he hands in front of us for 5 seconds, but one else did while we waited.

I have seen this not only here, but at other fast food establishments too.  Be careful!

Completely disappointed. Waited more then an hour for my order. I called to find out what happened but the girl who attended me from the beginning said my order couldn’t be found even when I gave my address and phone number. I would give this place 0 starts if I had the option to do so.

While not the most modern looking Pizza hut, it feels like a blast from the 1950s past, the good there is pretty on time and good. The lunch buffet is cheap and for the one time I went there, actually good. We've tried the hand tossed pizza, white sauce, chicken topping, and stuffed crust. The hand tossed tastes way better than the stuffed crust. The white sauce and chicken toppings are actually good!

Last Friday evening, I ordered online and came to pick up. The lady working alone was so hardworking, kind, prompt with my orders and the food was great. I ordered cheese personal pan pizzas for my kids and the tried the veggie lovers pizza for myself and it was fantastic.

The pizza was great. But please remind your drivers “asking or begging for a tip is not okay” that makes someone not want to give him or her a tip. I just ordered and when he delivered my order he says “can you add a tip” I said I don’t have cash… he says “well you paid with card” I said sorry I can’t today. I just had a baby last month I alway give tips out but right now I’m not doing it sorry. But anyway he says “well I work for the tip and rolls his eyes” that’s why I try not to order food because of that. Nobody wants to go through that when hungry and getting there food delivered. Now I’m really just picking up my orders. I hate when they do that. Please just teach them “begging for a tip is not the right way to go you’ll lose customers like that.”  I respect the driver for delivering my order I said thank you and all. Please it’s not okay.

Ordered a meatzilla pizza and 2 pasta bowls for delivery. Disappointed! Pizza had barely any toppings, primavera pasta bowl had thick slices of onion, barely any Spinach and not enough pasta. Chicken Alfredo was equally not as well put together.

Everything was correct unlike previous orders, everything came at one time (wasn't forgotten) unlike previous orders. Only things I can complain of this time is everything was cold except for the wings they were warm and the pizza with half cheese half pepperoni looks smashed or something that it's missing cheese, sauce, and the pepperonis.

Bad pizza experience at this store. This is my second bad experienece with the same store. They do not add cheese. Pizza contains just tomota sauce and hardly any cheese. Plus they DO NOT call when the pizza is ready for pickup or send any email/text for the same. I will not visit this location ever.

Complained about the same to store representative but received the coldest expression ever.

Spare your money and time and avoid this location.

We had a pizza snafu with this location. Even though our order was semi correct (the crust style was wrong), the reason for the one-star review is the poor customer service from the location’s manager, Brandon. He was extremely unprofessional. After I apologized for the error he couldn’t let it go. I chuck it up to that fact that he is very inexperienced and the fault really líes on the owner who’s responsibility is to guide their employees to provide excellent service.

Gianna was extremely unprofessional and rude. We placed and order online prior to coming into the store for pick up. She mispronounced the name on the order and told us it would be an additional 30 mins so we came back in 30 mins which was a lie. I asked her why she said 30 mins and she batted her eyes saying she doesn’t recall what she said. She bobbed her head around like a chicken and told us we can get fu%k out of the store. When we asked for her name she shouted her name and another worker told her to get the fu%k in the back of the store. It took the General Manager a few mins to come to try to fix the issue but the response time was unacceptable for the service we received. We will not be patronizing this establishment.
Gave me wrong order terrible service from older man and young light skin lady with tattoos they ignored me mostly and they acted bothered to help me on top no menus

“DO NOT ORDER FROM HERE” we ordered one pizza we received the wrong one, and then calling them took 20 minutes to get thru to someone. The second pizza was delivered a 1 hour and a half later. The quality seals were not holding the box closed. Looking now at the reviews which are mostly negative I should of read them first. I would of not had to experience this frustrating situation.

Ordered 8 pizzas for delivery AND pre-paid $30 tip for a 5min drive from the store. Placed the order 4 hours in advance. Called when it was 20mins late & was told “can’t give you ETA..it’s super bowl”. Umm what?! Of course you’ll have more orders on Super Bowl - PLAN for that and execute accordingly. Drove over to get my order that was just sitting there with apparently no worker motivated for a $30 tip - going to make sure to get my refund on that & never order from this location again.

Zero stars (but I had to put one)! Called to order and was told 45 minutes. Nearly 1.5 hours later- nothing has arrived. Spoke to a person that said they were the general manager. They were short and rude with me. This "manager" would place me on hold without even saying anything. When I called back to check on the status of my order, he put me on hold for 10 minutes before answering. When placing my order-I told him where to send the order and he did not confirm an address. He then said he sent it to another address when I called back. When I said- "I told you the name of the school, and you didn't ask for the address." He replied "I don't have the address to schools memorized." Surely he doesn't but he could have CONFIRMED the address. Then he said "I only have one driver, so it takes a while." While I understand the restaurant may be understaffed- it's best to be HONEST with customers about the delivery time. The "manager" ended the conversation by saying "oh, the driver just pulled up- it's going to be 15 minutes OKAY!" and then proceeded to HANG up the phone. No apologies, no patience. I will not be ordering from this location again. There are 4 other Papa John's in the area. You would think that this location would work hard to to stand out. Very disappointed.
Large inventory for a small store but they don't have any prices, so you have to walk everything up to the counter for the price.
Great place,variety of tobacco,great customer sevie ,all type of funnels and very reasonable peices as compare to neighbourhood.
Price gouging and did not apply 20 cents off on tuesday 5/24! What a rip off.
I’ve came here a lot. Nazim and the people in there are pretty nice and always greets familiar faces
Always competitively priced, but has, quite possibly, the worst pump layout imaginable. Also has no roof for those non-ideal weather days.

The food overall was good, but the only problem was that all of the tv’s had the same channel and i asked if they could change one of the tv channels to a basketball game going and they were like NO. I was really sad to hear this since the rest of the tv’s had the same exact channel and they couldn’t even change one to watch a college basketball game. :(
Have gotten take out pupusas several times. Always delicious! Call and order ahead. Good food takes time!
I will never order from here again. I ordered two baleadas one plain and one with beef . both were plain and cold . my drink was maracuya but tasted like plain water.  Wasted my money.

Pupusas we're good, I had also tried the taco de lengua which was delicious. The horchata was tasty and not grainy. The tamal de elote was good but the crema was sub par. Also the tomato base sauce was really watery which made the pupusas soggy.

Food always awesome
Our waitress was amazing she did a great job I hardly recommend this place.
Good portions.  Chicken seasoned very well. Chaufa was good.  Mac n Cheese needs some work.  Tasted like Stauffers.  Good value.  Overall would come back again.

The food is always good! The staff is very nice! The place is always clean,organized and cozy atmosphere! I usually order half chicken,plantain,white rice and fresh avocados! And sometimes I order shrimp salad! The food is also always hot and delicious 😋 😀🙂😘
Friendly establishment, food is very good. I love their fish fry so far and their charbroiled chicken is really good. Love their yucca and cucumber salad.
I really enjoyed their food. I had the estofado de pollo. The stew was flavorful. The rice was seasoned just enough. Also had the flan which was good. Fast service. I would come back

Food here is bomb. Fresh and in house. Love all the chicken dishes. Especially the one they slowly roast. Sides are typical you can't go wrong with their yuca fries or salads.

Theres plenty of seating for large parties and a wide open parking lot. Highly recommend this place for lunch or dinner. Food comes out quickly and well seasoned. They have plenty of flat screens for you to enjoy your meal and soccer game

This place gets the job done. It’s close to home and has a function drive through so it’s two thumbs up from this family!

I think the first time we visited was for a late night snack. So, just like most other McDonald’s, the hours are good. Lol.

Today we just needed something easy. We’d just completed the drive back from Reagan airport and I was exhausted and hungry. I definitely didn’t have the energy to sit and wait with my active children in a restaurant. So I was up for a drive through, fast food and back home.

They got our order right and of course it came out fast and hot.

I recommend the Big Mac. And I always add bacon.

Its a nice little McD in town. Theres a good amount of space and good service, nothing wild.

The food is exactly the same as you expect, the sausage egg mcmuffin tastes like a sausage egg mcmuffin. My hash brown was a bit old, but still crunchy, so no complaints.

My only issue is that the price of a hash brown was 2.39 for one! There is no way that you can tell me there is a potatoe shortage, theres no way it can be a political thing either, thats way beyond too much for potatoe...

I got to this McDonald's everyday because it's the closest to me but service here is really going down the drain. So I paid for a large fries and this is what I got. There is no fries in my bag so this is literally how they gave me my fries. When I order my coffee, i ask for 6 and 6, every single time there is no sugar in it barely. I understand it's fast food and it's not a big deal, but you taking my money and not giving good quality product is a big deal to me. Anyway, i just going to find another McDonald's i can trust. Thanks but no thanks.

Pretty good McDonalds, employees weren't overly friendly, but okay.  Food was good. Problem was older school kids taking up most of the tables hanging out & on their devices not really eating much and taking advantage of the free drink refills. The counter type seats were open, but not really comfortable for a "mature" customer who was there to dine, not socialize.  Just felt like management should have been aware of this and taken care of it so that it's a "fair" environment with no intimidation for all age customers.

I went in to buy a soda and take a leak. The bath was filthy and it took ten minutes of fiddling with a wonky order system to get a soda, then I had to cool my heels at the counter waiting for one of the geniuses to hand me a plastic cup so I draw my own soda.
At least the urinal flushed.

Busy. Staff efficient and friendly amongst "the weeds." And, DAMN!!! These red beans & rice with spicy 🔥 🍗 sandwich are 🔥🔥🔥 (HELLAGOOOOD)!!!
And these guys (& gals) were friendly, efficient and genuinely seemed to enjoy their environment and it shows.

I went on Popeyes website, put location (Wheaton) and it showed special $5 Big Box ( 2 pcs.+ 2 sides 1 biscuit ) so I printed that special out to shoe them. I showed the cashier before I order but they didn't honor that. They said the big box price is $6 !!!! I bought it anyway at least it's better than last time 8 dark meats thighs and wings for 19.99!!!! This time they gave me wrong side order too instead of fries and rice& bean, they gave me both rice&bean no fries 🍟 🙄 Someone need to check on them !!!!

Incredibly disgusting!!! Paid $12 for a white meat meal and got greasy, overly-breaded thigh, leg and wing! And to top it off, the food made me sick. I'll stick with Boston Market which would have been close in price but includes 1/2 healthy, non-greasy rotisserie chicken and two healthy vegetable choices! AVOID! AVOID! AVOID!

It was nice and clean. Despite being very busy the staff was nice and friendly. Our order was accurate and they were following social distancing guidelines. Thankful folks are keeping these restaurants open.
Not a good as it was many years ago, plus it’s pricey and you get less chicken and more breaded covering. Sweet tea is too sweet. Not a fan anymore.

Oh my goodness!!!!!!!! I am 6 months pregnant craving some bomb seafood and DAMN THIS FOOD SOME SHIIIITTTTTT!! Straight doodoo

Crab cakes does not taste like crab cakes, I make great crab cakes and I’m not a professional! The tarter sauce! YUCK!!! I’m upset my husband even got me this this!! Not trying to be disrespectful but this food taste like trash!! Never again! And if you order from here trust you will be mad. I never heard of this place before because I am not from this area, next time I will read reviews first!!!!!

Called to order two crab cake and 2 fillets of whiting with 2 sides. On Google maps the location info showed menu price of $13, in the store it was $19. Don't go by the online prices. The crab cakes are large and are fried cakes, NOT traditional lump and so not offer broiled option. Fish was good, crab cakes were okay.

Very Good Seafood at very fair prices! My wife and I came here for the first time and got some fish with shrimp to go. It only took them about 8 minutes to prepare. And I gotta say: it tastes better than I thought it would. I am Definitely going back to try their other things out. I must try their Crab Cakes and Lobsters. Give their food a try. Not bad at all!
Staff is friendly and food was hot and fresh. Wish they had the crinkle cut fries still but the food was good. 1st time getting the greens they were pretty good. Lol not like my mama's.
I bought a dozen and the largest ones cost me $89 and they were very skinny they had no meat inside I do not recommend it
Quality food and even better service! Great overall especially on their opening day! Staff cares and respects all customers.

First time customer & it was horrible! Do not order from here. I’ve had pupusas from all over & this was bad. We ordered pupusas revueltas, de queso and loroco. They tasted old like if they just popped it in the microwave. There was no filling. As you pull apart the pupusa the cheese doesn’t even “stretch.” They should also put the different types of pupusas in different boxes. We had to pull apart pupusas to distinguish them. I usually can tell which ones are revueltas, for example, but since there was barely any filling, you can’t even tell. The nuegados were okay. Never coming here again. This is the restaurant in Glenmont.

I would give this place one star if I had the option. I never give reviews but these people have no Idea how to treat people. If you don't speak Spanish be prepared to get the wrong food and terrible service. The cashier was on her cell phone as I made my order. She looked at me as if I was stupid so I grabbed a menu and showed her what I wanted. I'm almost positive it is wrong as my receipt is different compared to what I thought I had ordered.  I was over looked for another Latin patron even though I was standing at the register. No one asked me if I needed help as this was my first visit here. All the wile getting the look as if I don't belong in the presence of these people cause I wasn't Latin. I try to give places a chance but worst place I've been in a long time. Save your time, money and sanity don't bother with this place.

This place used to be really good. My family and I used to go here all the tile for the pupusas locals . Tonight we ordered 5 pupusas locas  a chicken soup and a grilled chicken breast on the side . We picked up the food, and we were so hungry that we eat it even though it was so bad. the chicken soup was all water and a couple of potatoe pieces  and nothing else.Also, the side chicken was like chicken wings !!!  Wrapped up in foil, hard stiff and the chicken looked like chicharron.The chicken was  fried and not grilled as they’d said over the phone .  We called the spot and they basically said they didn’t care if we were unhappy with the food because their restaurant is still popular so one unhappy customer won’t hurt them. Just sad . We won’t be coming here anymore .

The food quality and freshness needs to change for the better! The staff service horrible.. this restaurant would be an icon for Salvadorian food but the staff managing this establishment are doing such a bad job doing so. I would like to hear how everyone else’s experiences went. Leave a comment if you’d like to share!!
A bad place to refuel and to reset my 34 hours

Wow, I saw the reviews and decided to visit this food truck. Delicious high quality authentic Mexican food, great vibes, music and outdoor seating. You order from the smaller trucks and pick up at the bigger truck. We ordered several tacos and the pineapple Aguas frescas. I love the homemade fried tortillas. Beverages come in a pouch very fresh and tasty. Very busy, long lines, nice to see people outside enjoying tacos. I will be back to try more options from the menu. Definitely recommend, stop by if your in the area, you will not be disappointed.

My friend chose this spot to celebrate her birthday. We went Friday afternoon. Was able to place our order quickly and food was ready in about 10 minutes. I ordered the chorizo con papa which was big portioned and tasty! Friend had the 3 birria tacos and pineapple juice. Would definitely go again.

Amazing food! I have been seeing a lot of people eating outside of this truck for months now.
Ordered online and ate outside today on December 16th 😄. The best tacos I have ever had! Nachos were amazing too. Try Tacos Don Perez. You won’t be disappointed.
*edit* I had to add that the place was very CLEAN from what I have seen. Employees were wiping the outdoor tables immediately after a customer left and the kitchen looked very clean inside and out.
Plenty of utensils and napkins with my order.

Recommend this taco stand. Tried tacos and quesadilla. Both come packaged with radish, cucumber sides. Additional salsas inside have been good. It’s on the side of a gas station, and parking is plenty in the strip mall. Order at the window and adjacent truck does all the preparations. When the weather cooperates plenty of outside seating. My search for a go to taco stand is over, for the time being

Amazing Tacos! This is what Taco truck eating should Always be like. The Birria is awesome same with the AL Pastor. 3 Tacos 🌮 $11. Feel like I could have eaten 5 at least. They're kinda small (street tacos) but loaded with flavor. If You're ever in the Glenmont area, I highly recommend giving them a try. Right next to the Sunoco station.
I'll be back for sure👍

Absolute hidden Gem. Had two incredible dishes. The crispy pork is wonderful. If you like Korean food, check this place out.

Update. Went back and and two more. Hands down favorite. Must try the hot stone bibim bap!

A rule my good friend taught me, if you cant even read the sign outside, it must be good and authentic. I mean, the name outside is literally Korean, so you would never notice it easily without using Google Maps or a referral.

Nice little Korean Restaurant in this shopping center. The nice Korean decorations is cute, and the setting if fairly simple in design with no bells and whistles. The service is good and the speed is quick.

Tofu Soup: The tofu soup was not very spicy, so for those who can't handle spicy food, this dish will be a choice. It had a soft elegant aroma with very soft tofu. The seafood was pentiful, no shells like other places that throw the while muscle or shelled shrimp in it, so you can keep your fingers clean. The shrimp was tiny, not a average large size shrimp that an avid tofu soup eater would be used to, but it is actually easier to eat because you dont  have to take the shrimp out and peel it. Overall, great dish and the rich was soft and not too hard.

The pickled appetizers were good, fresh and crunchy, always good to have them.

Nice place to eat and maybe my go to place for tofu soup!

Best athentic Korean restaurant ever since I've moved to the states. The taste and flavor of food here took me back to Korea undoubtedly. Price was also reasonable, plus the owner was really nice. I'm planning to visit this place again on a regular base.
Should try!

One of the best Korean restaurants around to support! The service and takeout time is always fast, and the seullangtang is the best as it’s their specialty. It’s best especially in cold weather. Highly recommend to also get extra of their house made kimchi and kkakdoogi - I’m so picky with my kimchi and theirs is perfect with the flavour, tang, and freshness. Also not too salty and not too spicy if you’re not good with heat.
We went here for lunch, and I love their foods!

name: Kong Dog Korean style corndogs and bubble tea

html_attributions: Kong Dog Korean style corndogs and bubble tea

reviews.text: Tried first time. Not upset. I ordered Churro Kong Dog, with half beef sausage and cheddar, overall it was good, crispy and crunchy but cheese seem not as much as I expected. I also tried just an original Kong Dog, with half beef/mozzarella, it was ok. Seem too plain for me. Anyway their corn dog size is quite big and better quality from frozen package, of course the price is more. They also has fast food items like tenders, nuggets, fries. If you are a big fan of bubble tea, you can get it here, too. Even though it doesn't has many choices but still enough to try for street food truck style.

Nice location for quick, cheap eats. The food was good and they have a variety of options to choose from. Ordered the original kong dog and a potato kong dog, both with beef and mozzarella cheese. These dogs are very cheese and the beef is a decent portion. They were tasty and filling. I would come back here and order again.

The only reason I didn’t give them a 5 star because they don’t have any fountain drink and they only had a few selection of canned beverages.

Overall, def give them a try!

Simple, yet tasty and very fun to eat! However, the music was too loud, so it made it tougher to have a conversation. Along with a few other small issues (none of which were related to the food). There were no problems that couldnt be ironed out easily.

Considering the place just opened I suspect the experience will only improve with time, and I definitely would reccomend anyone nearby or just anyone who wants to try a Korean corn dog to come down and give Kong Dog a chance.

(Plus it's vegetarian friendly with their cheese corn dogs!)

Really good! My boyfriend got the sweet potato hot dog and the special fries (I can’t remember the name), but they were regular fries with hot Cheetos dust, Parmesan cheese and melted cheese. It was all really good. It looked better than it was, BUT it looked REALLY good.

Let’s just say that we saw a TiKTok and went for the experience. They have a variety of toppings/combinations to choose from but o didn’t find it to be special. The dogs tasted just regular corn dogs you could find at a Fair to me. Bubble tea is not my thing but that Strawberry Lemonade was banging.

This is a really solid Starbucks location. The service is good and the drive thru operates smoothly in my experience.

All of my drinks from here have been of good quality with no issues.

The one downside is that if you enter the shopping center area in the wrong place it can be difficult to get into the line. Also, when you exit it can be a little challenging to get where you want to go. But not a big deal.

Looking at the lowest rated reviews, it is clear I am not the only one to notice the consistently-subpart service offered here. Though the space is nice and low-key, the poor attitude of the baristas is driving me away. The nonchalance in everything they do is nauseating!
Very upsetting, i depend on my coffee in the morning and this is what I see in my cup. The sand which was pretty good though.

Took me 20 minutes to get my order they were busy with the drive thru, I don't know if that had something to do with my order taking so long but I did see that one of my orders was just sitting on the counter not the counter where you pick up.
This Starbucks is great.  My drinks are always accurate.  It's close to home and has a drivethru.  Friendly staff.

There’s not a lack of taco spots in the D.C. area. Well I found one that has something I’ve never seen before. A pupusa PIZZA?? Ok…I was on the first flight out to Wheaton. Let’s go see what this joint is hittin on!!
.
Where I am: @trippytacos240
.
Location Reviewed: 12134 Georgia Ave., Silver Spring M.D.
.
Menu Includes:
Street Tacos, Burritos, Tortas, Nachos, Quesadillas, Mulitas, Topped Fries, Pupusa’s, Beverages, Chips, & Salsa.
.
Items Reviewed:
Their Chicken Trippy Nachos (with chicken, Guac, nacho cheese, crema, jalapeños, Pico de Gallo, & Trippy sauce $14.50). STAMP!! This wasn’t aesthetically pleasing, but, the chips were thin, & fresh, & the sweet Trippy sauce gave these nachos a distinctively sweet, & savory flavor!!

Their Birria Burrito (with beef Birria, rice, beans, cheese, Pico de Gallo, Crema, consumé & Trippy sauce $13.50). STAMP!! Fresh, meaty, dipped in that consumé…WINNING!!

Their Tacos-All tacos come on a corn tortilla with melted cheese, onions, cilantro, lime, hot, & mild sauce.
Chicken Taco ($3.49)
Al Pastor Taco ($3.49)
Steak Taco ($3.99)
ALL DELICIOUS!! Meaty but bland w/o the hot red & green sauce…but tasty with it.

Their 16” Pupusa Pizza Revuelta (with cheese, sauce, cabbage, & pork $27.99). LIKE THAT!! This pie was HUGE, flavorful, & dense with marinated pulled pork. The cabbage, & sauce set this off!!
.
Customer Service: On Point
.
Online Navigation: Easy
.
Parking: Plentiful
.
Recommendations: Try the Pupusa pizza, Nachos, & Birria Burrito!!

#Bigschlimsreviews

Solid tacos, cramped seating, friendly service.

Sampled the al pastor, carne asada, and pollo. The pollo was forgettable in flavor but decent quality chicken, and was nice with either salsa. The carne asada was similar, a little more flavorful and decent quality, and food with the salsa verde. The al pastor was by far the best, didn't need any salsa to make up for flavor and had good quality pork.

I am sure the quality extends similarly to the other dishes based on the filling.

They have some tight counter bar stool seating right next to the order counter, it's basically a to go business but you can grab a quick bite there.

Nice service, friendly folks.

For Mexican food in MoCo, it rates above average.

The pork and cheese pupusa was excellent. Very fluffy which soaked up a lot of the pork and cheese flavors. The carne asada Trippy Nachos were decent. Plenty of toppings for all the chips, but I wish they would use real cheese instead of “nacho cheese”. Especially because the rest of the ingredients are so fresh.

I loved the place we frequented them because we work in the area the food was delicious we came back the place has been renovated it has a new image but the service is lousy we ordered 2 orders of carne asada burritos to go while the person prepared another order for us to go chicken I used to love the staff we asked for the burritos we saw how they prepared the meat and added the ingredients surprise she was dissatisfied with the way she was being served, but the terrible thing was the taste when she received my burritos she did not know what she had eaten before where is she my carne asada today was prepared meat not roasted, the cheese was cold, the taste was ugly the taste of the vegetables and cheese cooked on the griddle was missing I really loved ☹ the burritos of this place today all its ingredients are cold the taste of the rice it's not nice

We both had a quesadilla from this new storefront location. Enjoyable food, nice size portions but not overwhelming, and quality ingredients. The online ordering worked well, and pickup service was efficient and friendly. Everything looked clean and you can see the food being prepared. We look forward to trying tacos and pupusas on our next visit.

I got two tacos de rey and they where salty, no hot sauce for the tacos.
I also ordered 2 pupusas revueltas and 1 beans and cheese, they where taste less. The tomato sauce that goes with it has not taste and feels like water. The food was expensive, I placed the order and was not told the total. I will never go back again, worst tacos and pupusas I’ve had in my life. I’m Salvadorian so we know good food but there’s was not at all. Either too salty or no taste at all.

This place is not the place to get a Lomo Saltado. Let’s first start off with the fact that one of the employees touched my food with her bare hands, because she was putting it on the container without gloves! Secondly they put rice under and placed the lomo salado on top! I personally don’t like my food to be all together in one place— I prefer separation. The food is too salty, the rice is yellow charbroiled rice not even  WHITE Jasmine or basmati.... I really am disappointed with the place. It’s my first time trying it and I will never go back again.

Place looks nice but not everything on their menu has posted the price. When i ordered she took the order and did not tell me how much it was. I ordered sopa de res (was listed) and bailadas(was not) a little pricy($8.99 found out when i asked for the recept. Once i had it the beef was a little rubbery and had to chew) I tried the sopa de res. It wasn't that great. It cost 11.99 meat was also hard and chewy and the carrots were still under cooked. The soup (water part) just tasted like salt water not much flavor.

The pupusas are huge and tasty for the price! Very filling. I would recommend the revueltas pupusas and the bean and cheese pupusas. Sidenote: make sure you know how to say what you want in Spanish because the staff does not know much English.
They make the best Papusas ever!!! The ladies are so sweet!!!
The lengua sold here is just on another level. Very tender not chewy and absolutely delicious! Great customer service, decent prices, yummy food...can't beat that!
We got the lomo saltado and pollo saltado. They were both delicious and came with delicious fries! Would visit again.

Had a 1/4 chicken and yuca on side. Yuca pieces were huge and so yummy. I wish those were smaller. Spicy and cheesy yuca sauces are not that great. It was clean and staff was really friendly. Took about 10 mins to get us the fresh yuca. Parking is available. Was little busy evening around 5 pm.
The chicken is good.  There are a lot of sides dishes.  The restaurant is clean. Staff is nice. The portion and price are reasonable.
Lengua Asada! Yum!! Huge portions, service is fast and cooks are extremely nice.
